"title": "7316: blood, and OT sacrifices",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7316",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The pouring out of animals' blood in sacrifice was God's provision, under the old covenant, for the atonement of sin.</p>\n<h2>God's provision of blood sacrifice to establish the old covenant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4-Exod24:8\">EXO 24:4–24:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:18-Heb9:20\">HEB 9:18–9:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's provision of blood sacrifices within the old covenant</h2>\n<h3>Blood sacrifices and the priesthood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:10-Exod29:21\">EXO 29:10–29:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:14-Lev8:24\">LEV 8:14–8:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:8-Lev9:14\">LEV 9:8–9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:1-Lev16:14\">LEV 16:1–16:14</a></p>\n<h3>Blood sacrifices and various offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:1-Lev1:17\">LEV 1:1–1:17</a> <em>the burnt offering, to gain favour or express devotion</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:1-Lev3:17\">LEV 3:1–3:17</a> <em>the fellowship, or peace, offering, to express gratitude</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:1-Lev4:35\">LEV 4:1–4:35</a> <em>the sin offering, to gain forgiveness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:14-Lev5:19\">LEV 5:14–5:19</a> <em>the guilt offering, where restitution was required</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:15-Lev16:22\">LEV 16:15–16:22</a> <em>the Day of Atonement, for the cleansing of the nation from unintentional sin</em></p>\n<h3>Blood sacrifices and the Passover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:1-Exod12:14\">EXO 12:1–12:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:15-2Chr30:20\">2CH 30:15–30:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:1-2Chr35:19\">2CH 35:1–35:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:19-Ezra6:21\">EZR 6:19–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:12\">MRK 14:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:7-Luke22:8\">LUK 22:7–22:8</a></p>\n<h2>Blood sacrifices must come from animals without defect</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:17-Lev22:25\">LEV 22:17–22:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:5\">EXO 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:3\">LEV 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:1\">LEV 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:3\">LEV 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:15\">LEV 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:9\">NUM 28:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:11\">NUM 28:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:21\">DEU 15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:22-Ezek43:27\">EZK 43:22–43:27</a></p>\n<h2>Blood sacrifices must not come from human beings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:10\">2KI 23:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:17\">2KI 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:1-2Kgs21:6\">2KI 21:1–21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:25-Ezek20:26\">EZK 20:25–20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:7\">MIC 6:7</a></p>\n<h2>The limited effect of blood sacrifices</h2>\n<h3>They can become mere external ritual</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11-Isa1:13\">ISA 1:11–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:2-Isa66:4\">ISA 66:2–66:4</a></p>\n<h3>They are worthless without obedience to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:6\">HOS 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:22-1Sam15:23\">1SA 15:22–15:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:6-Ps40:8\">PSA 40:6–40:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:4-Amos4:5\">AMO 4:4–4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:21-Amos5:27\">AMO 5:21–5:27</a></p>\n<h3>They are unable to cleanse the conscience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:9-Heb9:10\">HEB 9:9–9:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:1-Heb10:4\">HEB 10:1–10:4</a></p>",
